        "content": "{\n  \"resolution_strategies\": [\n    {\n      \"resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS1_INSERT_REJECTION_CHECK_AFTER_CONDUCT\",\n      \"change_operations\": \"1. In the consented branch, inside the assessment sequence, replace the subsequence 'conduct interview and questionnaire; direct questions; exclusive(rejected -> inform of rejection; terminate, not rejected -> prepare for venepuncture...)' with 'conduct interview and questionnaire; exclusive(rejected -> inform of rejection; terminate, not rejected -> direct questions; exclusive(rejected -> inform of rejection; terminate, not rejected -> prepare for venepuncture...))'. 2. Ensure every occurrence of 'inform of rejection' is directly followed by 'terminate'.\",\n      \"evaluation\": {\n        \"compliance_degree\": {\n          \"value\": \"full\",\n          \"reason\": \"If 'conduct interview and questionnaire' sets assessment_status to rejected, the new immediately following exclusive branch executes 'inform of rejection' and then 'terminate'. If 'direct questions' later sets the status to rejected, the existing rejection branch still handles it.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"high\",\n          \"reason\": \"The strategy preserves the consent handling, the resources assigned to the assessment activities, the parallel relation between 'retract consent' and the assessment branch, and the timed alternative involving 'monitor patient' and 'assess donor'.\"\n        },\n        \"change_cost\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"The change is localized but requires restructuring the assessment sequence and duplicating the rejection-handling branch.\"\n        },\n        \"structural_quality_impact\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"The process remains block-structured, but an additional nested exclusive gateway and duplicated 'inform of rejection; terminate' sequence increase structural complexity.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"middle\",\n          \"reason\": \"The change is located in the middle assessment part of the consented process branch, after consent has been obtained and before venepuncture.\"\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS2_INTRODUCE_STICKY_REJECTION_FLAG\",\n      \"change_operations\": \"1. Before 'conduct interview and questionnaire', initialize a persistent data flag, for example data.rejection_detected = false. 2. Extend both 'conduct interview and questionnaire' and 'direct questions' so that whenever they write assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\", they also set data.rejection_detected = true. 3. Modify the rejection exclusive condition from 'data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\"' to 'data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\" or data.rejection_detected'. 4. Modify the opposite branch condition to the logical negation of the new rejection condition. 5. Keep 'inform of rejection' directly followed by 'terminate'.\",\n      \"evaluation\": {\n        \"compliance_degree\": {\n          \"value\": \"full\",\n          \"reason\": \"Once the rejected condition becomes true at any point during the assessment, the sticky flag preserves that fact until the existing rejection decision point is reached, ensuring that 'inform of rejection' eventually occurs and is directly followed by 'terminate'.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"high\",\n          \"reason\": \"The existing control-flow order, resource assignments, parallel structure, consent handling, and timed alternative are preserved. The strategy only adds data-state tracking.\"\n        },\n        \"change_cost\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"The control-flow structure is not changed, but several data annotations and branch conditions must be updated consistently.\"\n        },\n        \"structural_quality_impact\": {\n          \"value\": \"low\",\n          \"reason\": \"The process tree remains structurally unchanged. The main impact is additional data logic, not additional gateways or duplicated activities.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"middle\",\n          \"reason\": \"The changes are confined to the assessment-status handling in the middle of the consented branch.\"\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS3_PREVENT_DIRECT_QUESTIONS_FROM_OVERWRITING_REJECTION\",\n      \"change_operations\": \"1. Refine the data-write behavior of 'direct questions' so that it must not overwrite an existing data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\" with a non-rejected value. 2. Allow 'direct questions' to keep writing assessment_status when the current value is not rejected, including writing assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\" if appropriate. 3. Keep the existing exclusive branch after 'direct questions' unchanged, with 'data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\"' leading to 'inform of rejection; terminate'.\",\n      \"evaluation\": {\n        \"compliance_degree\": {\n          \"value\": \"full\",\n          \"reason\": \"If 'conduct interview and questionnaire' sets assessment_status to rejected, that value can no longer be erased before the existing rejection decision point. If 'direct questions' sets assessment_status to rejected, the existing branch already informs of rejection and terminates.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"high\",\n          \"reason\": \"All existing activities, resource assignments, parallel relations, direct-follow relations, and timed behavior are preserved. 'direct questions' still receives and can write assessment_status, but its write behavior is constrained to preserve rejection.\"\n        },\n        \"change_cost\": {\n          \"value\": \"low\",\n          \"reason\": \"Only one localized data-effect constraint on 'direct questions' is required. No control-flow restructuring or activity duplication is needed.\"\n        },\n        \"structural_quality_impact\": {\n          \"value\": \"none\",\n          \"reason\": \"The structured tree shape is unchanged. The modification only refines data semantics.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"middle\",\n          \"reason\": \"The change is located at 'direct questions' in the assessment part of the consented branch.\"\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS4_REMOVE_CONDUCT_AS_REJECTION_STATUS_SOURCE\",\n      \"change_operations\": \"1. Modify 'conduct interview and questionnaire' so that it no longer writes directly to data.assessment_status. 2. If the activity still needs to record an intermediate result, make it write to a different data object such as data.preliminary_assessment_status. 3. Preserve any required receive or consume relation for assessment_status on 'conduct interview and questionnaire'. 4. Leave 'direct questions' as the activity that writes the final assessment_status before the existing rejection exclusive branch.\",\n      \"evaluation\": {\n        \"compliance_degree\": {\n          \"value\": \"substantial\",\n          \"reason\": \"The identified violation is mitigated because 'conduct interview and questionnaire' can no longer make assessment_status become rejected before 'direct questions'. The remaining writer, 'direct questions', is already followed by the rejection decision. However, this assumes the business semantics allow rejection to be determined only after 'direct questions'.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"The listed context requirements can be preserved, especially if the receive relation for assessment_status remains. However, the meaning of 'conduct interview and questionnaire' is changed more significantly than in the other strategies